values:
wait I have a livejournal? what? 

I used to write in this thing every day, sometimes twice a day. And I mean straight up pour out my soul kind of writing, and I would somehow find some deep revelation about myself while i was writing. ya know???!!!! Now I sit here, last update over a year ago, a lot going on, but not sure how to write in this format anymore haha.

I am in Schaumburg again, first time in a loonngg time. I love Texas and am pretty ready to just get back there. Schaumburg doesn't have too much to offer. I think I am actually going to go back to the high school tomorrow. Wierd, right? I just want to see the choir. and then peace out. Oh and Atchison of course because I love her. Possibly Pennisi just to brag about my new teaching position.

Oh yes, I am a teacher now. I teach the astronomy labs at good ole UNT. I run the big dome planetarium, teach student proper use of telescopes and computer based telescopes, as well as point out some pretty kick ass things to look at in the sky, and telescope simulators through the computer lab. loves it.

Stephanie Stephens is still the love of my life. 

I might be going to Ireland for spring semester 2009. Possibly with Lindsay Bukiet!!!! Which is actualy a complete coinicidence that we picked the same university at the same time. fingers crossed.

Still doing choir at the university, but no longer a music major. Literature major, very happy with it. Can't you tell English is my major by my abundant use of sentence fragments?

Juno is the best movie I have seen in a long time. Besides Across the Universe.

but Buffy the Vampire Slayer remains the best TV show ever. 

My sister is having her last surgery hopefully ever next weekend. Just getting scar tissue removed from her other cancer surgeries. So thats gooooooood. My niece is now 5 inches taller than me and wears size 11 shoe. WTF?! 

I have still been working at Sunrise Assisted Living and its been pretty good for me. A very rewarding job I suppose. today was my last day though so it will be nice to relax this last week I am home.

I have an apartment and an adorable kitten. I dont think I'm going to keep living there next year though. Maybe a house? maybe?

I feel like doing something crazy. Like a spontaneous road trip, like breaking into that place that makes swimming pools and getting attacked by guard dogs. Oh wait that wasnt fun at all...

haha but something along those lines.

I also have a craving to obtain new music. New good music that is super indie and super underground. you know the type. And to get new tattoos and piercings. And all of these cravings are incredibly strong. Maybe later this week. I am a very spontaneous tattoo-getter. Hopefully this doesnt end in regret.

Well, this has been the end of my yearly update. Please notice that there is no mention of a love life. Just a note to myself when I look back on this later haha. I hope it was random enough for anyone who still reads this thing. I know I feel no better nor worse for writing it. 

ummm peace out? :)

I don't actually know who still reads these, but I just wanted to get a few thoughts out and let whoever is still living in the livejournal community know that I am alive and well in Texas.

It is really strange being so far away from the people that I really care about. But I guess that's what I wanted right? I wanted to come here and make myself feel complete without having other people complete me. I am perfectly aware how dramatic that sounds, but regardless, it is true. And I think I am acheiving what I wanted. I'm having a lot of fun down here, and Texans are all so nice. It's almost like a completely different culture. People seriously care about each other. I never realized what a difference that would make in a community or in people's lives.

So, I ran away from Ilinois and I don't intend on visiting often. How can a place be such a hell hole yet at the same time be my home? And why am I asking that question when I already know the answer. The people I love are in Illinois. Wherever they happened to be, that would be home.

I also wanted to comment that it's funny how sometimes God cannot be more obvious about where he wants you to go. One can try every road, every path, and every possible means to try and get their own agenda completed. But he will close door after door and burn every bridge, until the only way left for you to go is crawling through a window. There is no such thing as a coincidence.

Although these thoughts of mine are jumbled, confusing, and probably contradicatory, I want it to be said that I am enjoying myself immensely here. My classes are easy and boring right now, but I'm hoping that will change as the semester continues. I joined choir, and that is keeping me really busy, but I aboslutely love it. I applied for an internship with the Student Government Association here at UNT and I find out today if I got it or not. I am also thinking about  joining a literature club. I am trying to build up the courage to join a church here on campus. I love my roomates, and I love the weather. So really, I cannot complain about anything.

I have decided that this December I'm donating my hair to Locks of Love. I want to go help in New Orleans for Spring Break. I want to graduate in 3 years and then go on to graduate school. I want to spend a year as a missionary, and I want to adopt 2 children.

Where those thoughts came from, I have no idea.

I hope everyone is well and i miss ya'll! (I'm sorry, I had to say it! I'm a Texan now).   :)

This weekend was amazing.

And I am going to go out on a limb and say that today was a good day. Not because everything in it was good, but because i have begun to consider any day that enhances life, even if it's sometimes negative, as a good day. 

My job has become very emotionally stressful. I work at an assisted living home, and it is very easy to get attached to the residents. Death is a very common thing in places like my job, yet death never ceases to be sorrowful. I hope that I never say that working at an assisted living home has made me "used" to death, because I have honestly seen so much in this year that I've worked there and I'm still not used to it. Although, after knowing some of these amazing people i better understand that death really is part of life. I won't ever forget Marion Edwards holding my hand. I never thought one could look at a person and see death; i never thought that one could actually see life slipping away. 

In lighter news, I went to the bookstore today afterwork, because i just really needed it. I bought a book for Kevin and I bought A Handmaid's Tale because I'm doing it for my AP project. Then, on my way out the door I passed by a table where books were advertised as being $3!!!! I serioulsy ran back to the register and purchased 3 of the best feminine classics a feline can by: Emma, Anna Karenina, and Vanity Fair. I left the bookstore elated, all serious thoughts of life, death, and other nonsense completely forgotten.

I do believe i am the ultimate nerd.

And-tomorrow is late start. I couldn't be happier
On Saturday night, i went to a galla at the field museum. I am a big nerd and I love the field museum so this was rather exciting. It was quite....interesting. and I will leave it at that.

All we're doing is wasting time.

You'll sit alone forever if you wait for the right time
What are you hoping for?
I'm here, right now, I'm ready.
Holding on tight
Don't give em the end
The one thing that stays mine.

I haven't listened to John Mayer in forever! I almost forgot about his wonderfulness

I spent this evening walking around the mall by myself and pondering my shitty day, and I decided that i have had some great moments in life, and i have "lived in the now," and i have all these little bits of memories and accomplishments and peices of life. however, in the end if they don't fit together to make a big picture, i really don't have anything at all. 

So my point is i have some work to do. 

I am going to visit U of I this weekend and it is going to be a fun and lovely loop to add to this rollercoaster i like to call life. Exactly what i need i hope

Time to read! goodnight

my brother's best friend died yesterday. He was 19. Young people shouldnt die.

The End
